# SKYETECH Sovereign Primitives — SkyeHawk

## Status note — shelved until IDEia builds are complete
As of 2026-03-19, SkyeHawk has partial wiring inside the SkyeCDE hub and shared IDEia shell.

That work should be treated as a parked feature branch of the platform idea, not as proof that the IDEia builds are ready.

The fix order from here is:
- finish the IDEias as enterprise-grade product lanes first
- keep the current SkyeHawk wiring stable but deprioritized
- come back later to harden or prune the SkyeHawk implementation once the product builds are actually complete

This note exists so the current wiring is not mistaken for release readiness.

## What SkyeHawk is in plain English
SkyeHawk is the sovereign system menu and navigation layer.

Its job is simple:
- give the user one place to open the rest of the system
- let the user move between apps without hunting through random sidebars
- provide a hidden or power-user entry path when a normal menu is not visible
- act like a command deck, not just a decorative button

If the 0s is the operating ecosystem, SkyeHawk is the thing that helps users move through it.

