## What SkyeHawk actually does inside a platform
Inside a platform, SkyeHawk should do five jobs:

1. Navigation
It moves the user to apps, lanes, tools, recovery surfaces, and hub pages.

2. Discovery
It shows users what exists, even when the normal UI does not expose everything clearly.

3. Power-user entry
It gives advanced users a hidden command path or gesture path to open the system menu fast.

4. Route normalization
It prevents every platform from inventing a different launcher behavior.

5. Trust-aware exposure
It should only expose privileged destinations when the session/role/policy allows them.

