## What is still not built
This is the section that needs to be explicit.

SkyeHawk is **not** platform-wide yet.

What exists right now is fragmented:
- SuperIDE has a visible SkyeHawk rail pattern
- Neural Space Pro has a visible launcher + popup guidance pattern
- SkaixuPro-IDE has the strongest hidden-command implementation
- SkyeCDE does **not** yet have a real SkyeHawk command layer wired into the hub or the IDEia lanes
- there is **not** one shared route registry for the full 0s system yet
