## Full implementation backlog

### 1. Shared route registry
Need one canonical SkyeHawk route registry for the whole 0s.

That registry needs to include:
- route id
- display label
- canonical href
- route category
- source platform
- privilege level
- visibility mode
- aliases and command phrases
- whether the route is user-safe, operator-only, admin-only, or recovery-only

Until this exists, every platform is inventing its own partial route list.

### 2. Shared command grammar
Need one set of supported command phrases.

Examples:
- `skyehawk`
- `open menu`
- `show system`
- `open skydexia`
- `open current superide`
- `show recovery lanes`
- `show admin surfaces`

Until this exists, SkyeHawk behavior will remain inconsistent across platforms.

### 3. Shared hidden-entry contract
Need one policy for how SkyeHawk opens invisibly.

Possible supported methods:
- keyboard shortcut
- gesture trigger
- typed command trigger
- command-palette entry

This needs to be standardized so the hidden command is not different in every product.

### 4. Shared visible-entry contract
Need one policy for how visible SkyeHawk controls should appear.

That includes:
- launcher button placement
- menu rail placement
- popup guidance behavior
- first-run teaching behavior
- dismiss / persistence behavior

Until this is standardized, SkyeHawk will feel like three unrelated UI experiments.

### 5. SkyeCDE integration
Need to wire SkyeHawk directly into SkyeCDE.

That means:
- add a SkyeHawk trigger to the SkyeCDE hub
- add a hidden SkyeHawk command entry to the SkyeCDE hub
- add SkyeHawk entry inside the shared IDEia shell
- expose SkyeCDE hub, all IDEia lanes, and original preserved product surfaces through SkyeHawk

Without this, SkyeCDE may exist in the catalog but still is not part of the system-menu experience.

### 6. IDEia lane wiring
Need each IDEia lane to register itself into SkyeHawk.

Minimum destinations:
- SkyeCDE hub
- SkyDexia
- SuperIDEia
- SkaixuProIDEia
- KaixuSuperIDEia
- original SkyDex
- original SuperIDE
- original SkaixuPro-IDE
- original KaixuSuper-IDE

This should not be hardcoded differently in every lane.

### 7. Role and policy filtering
Need SkyeHawk to hide privileged routes when the user is not allowed to see them.

This includes:
- admin routes
- recovery routes
- operator routes
- gateway control routes
- vault-governed routes

Until this is enforced, SkyeHawk is a launcher, not a trustworthy sovereign navigation layer.

### 8. Search and command routing engine
Need SkyeHawk to resolve:
- route names
- aliases
- fuzzy search
- typed navigation requests
- category browsing

That engine should route users to the correct destination instead of depending on one-off click handlers.

### 9. Cross-platform event contract
Need SkyeHawk open/route actions to emit a shared event envelope.

That should include:
- who opened SkyeHawk
- which route was selected
- from which source surface
- with what role/policy context
- whether the route required privilege elevation

Without this, SkyeHawk is not integrated into sovereign telemetry.

### 10. Recovery and operations surface support
Need SkyeHawk to expose more than public app links.

It should eventually route to:
- recovery lanes
- operator lanes
- admin lanes
- audit surfaces
- vault and release control surfaces

This is the difference between a menu and an operating-system command layer.

### 11. Documentation and truth discipline
Need the docs to clearly separate three states:
- pattern exists
- baseline is wired
- full system is complete

That distinction was not clear enough before.

