## Relationship to the unfinished IDEias
This also needs to be stated directly.

The IDEias were moved through a **verified baseline parity pass**.

That baseline meant:
- lane-owned module split
- workspace controls
- file controls
- runtime controls
- state persistence
- launch mapping
- preserved link back to original product

That baseline did **not** mean:
- fully product-specific enterprise workflows are complete
- full SkyeHawk integration is complete
- admin/recovery/operator route systems are complete
- role-aware system-menu behavior is complete
- deep product-native lane features are complete

So if the question is "why was work moved forward if SkyDexia was not fully done," the honest answer is:
- the stopping line was set at baseline parity verification, not final enterprise completion
- that is why the work advanced to the next lanes
- that baseline/final distinction should have been stated more clearly

